Install expansion tank or other approved device (pressure relief valve set @ 100lbs ( house side)), test RPZ and perform CCT, label per PDR ( Purple box lids, hose bibs labeled non-potable if tied to well) check all boxes that apply. If city backup is to be used for irrigation another RPZ must be installed and tested. If not, the existing BFP must be removed and the lines capped. If the RPZ needs to be relocated as to avoid damage or for aesthetics an Alternate Method Form will need to be filled out explaining where it is to be located and submitted to our office. The extension from the meter will have to be sleeved with a larger pipe and labeled POTABLE WATER or wrapped in plastic and capped with 3" of concrete. The method and location chosen will need to be explained in the Alternate Method Form.
